    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 6C: in NCAM-/-, which disrupts AP2-based SV endocytosis, pulldowns of synaptophysin from crude SV fractions yielded a strong increase in AP-3. This suggests an increase of endocytosis via AP3 pathways.\n\nFigure 7. AP3-mediated bulk membrane retrieval was enhanced in NCAM-/- synaptic boutons.\n\nFigure 8. AP3-dependent synaptic vesicle endocytosis and intrasynaptic processing are upregulated in NCAM-/- synaptic boutons.\n\nThe antibody for AP3 targeted AP3B2.. Experimental description: M&M: \"To prepare cultures of hippocampal neurons, 1- to 3-d-old C57BL/6J and NCAM-/- mice of either sex from homozygous breeding pairs were used.\"\n\nantibody:\n\"neuronal adaptin-like protein beta (βNAP) subunit of AP-3 (clone 18, catalog #610892)\"\nnote; this is AP3B2",
